Download logo Shri V. Muraleedharan, Minister of State for External Affairs and Parliamentary Affairs held a virtual meeting with H.E. Dr. Frederick Shava, Minister of Foreign Affairs and International Trade of the Republic of Zimbabwe on Monday, 28th June 2021. Both Ministers discussed a diverse range of bilateral, regional and multilateral issues of interest to both sides. Matters related to trade & investment and ways to strengthen these were also discussed. Recalling the historical ties between both the countries, the two Ministers reiterated their commitment to further strengthen the bilateral relationship. Distributed by APO Group on behalf of Ministry of External Affairs â€“ Government of India.